item.title: Privacy Policy
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Who we are

Our website address is: http://websitestaging.tk/523studios.

What personal data we collect and why we collect it

Comments

When visitors leave comments on the site we collect the data shown in the comments form, and also the visitor’s IP address and browser user agent string to help spam detection.

An anonymized string created from your email address (also called a hash) may be provided to the Gravatar service to see if you are using it. The Gravatar service privacy policy is available here: https://automattic.com/privacy/. After approval of your comment, your profile picture is visible to the public in the context of your comment.

Media

If you upload images to the website, you should avoid uploading images with embedded location data (EXIF GPS) included. Visitors to the website can download and extract any location data from images on the website.

Contact forms

Cookies

If you leave a comment on our site you may opt-in to saving your name, email address and website in cookies. These are for your convenience so that you do not have to fill in your details again when you leave another comment. These cookies will last for one year.

If you visit our login page, we will set a temporary cookie to determine if your browser accepts cookies. This cookie contains no personal data and is discarded when you close your browser.

When you log in, we will also set up several cookies to save your login information and your screen display choices. Login cookies last for two days, and screen options cookies last for a year. If you select "Remember Me", your login will persist for two weeks. If you log out of your account, the login cookies will be removed.

If you edit or publish an article, an additional cookie will be saved in your browser. This cookie includes no personal data and simply indicates the post ID of the article you just edited. It expires after 1 day.

Embedded content from other websites

Articles on this site may include embedded content (e.g. videos, images, articles, etc.). Embedded content from other websites behaves in the exact same way as if the visitor has visited the other website.

These websites may collect data about you, use cookies, embed additional third-party tracking, and monitor your interaction with that embedded content, including tracking your interaction with the embedded content if you have an account and are logged in to that website.

Analytics

Who we share your data with

How long we retain your data

If you leave a comment, the comment and its metadata are retained indefinitely. This is so we can recognize and approve any follow-up comments automatically instead of holding them in a moderation queue.

For users that register on our website (if any), we also store the personal information they provide in their user profile. All users can see, edit, or delete their personal information at any time (except they cannot change their username). Website administrators can also see and edit that information.

What rights you have over your data

If you have an account on this site, or have left comments, you can request to receive an exported file of the personal data we hold about you, including any data you have provided to us. You can also request that we erase any personal data we hold about you. This does not include any data we are obliged to keep for administrative, legal, or security purposes.

Where we send your data

Visitor comments may be checked through an automated spam detection service.

Your contact information

Additional information

How we protect your data

What data breach procedures we have in place

What third parties we receive data from

What automated decision making and/or profiling we do with user data

Industry regulatory disclosure requirements

item.title: About
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: [vc_row][vc_column][vc_single_image image="98" img_size="full" alignment="center" el_class="inner-banner"][vc_row_inner el_class="inner-page-content"][vc_column_inner][vc_custom_heading text="ABOUT 523studios" font_container="tag:p|text_align:center" use_theme_fonts="yes" el_class="inner-page-title"][vc_column_text el_class="inner-page-desc"]523studios is a 1000-square-foot natural light studio and creative space in the heart of Buckhead in Atlanta, Georgia. Designed by natural light child and family photographer Alice Park, this all-white studio was thoughtfully set up to coordinate with and enhance your work. Everything, from the direction the studio windows face, to the clean white hardwood floors, to the ideal hue on the walls, was intentionally planned by an experienced photographer who used her creativity and love of design to bring this space to life.[/vc_column_text][vc_custom_heading text="ABOUT KYU & ALICE" font_container="tag:p|text_align:center" use_theme_fonts="yes" el_class="inner-page-title"][vc_column_text el_class="inner-page-desc"]Kyu and Alice Park are decade-long photography business owners who long had a vision for 523studios. In 2009, they intuitively founded the National Association of Professional Child Photographers (NAPCP), with the belief in the idea of creating an encouraging and uplifting professional culture that, above all, is about community. This innovative, collaborative and entrepreneurial approach is what now defines 523studios. 523studios is distinct in that we believe in organic connections and the cultivation and development of thoughtful ideas and relationships.[/vc_column_text][vc_custom_heading text="ABOUT THE CREATIVES WHO USE THIS SPACE" font_container="tag:p|text_align:center" use_theme_fonts="yes" el_class="inner-page-title"][vc_column_text el_class="inner-page-desc"]Lest you worry that only photographers utilize 523studios, there is nothing we love more than converting this stunning “white box” into a sophisticated business space for professionals with discerning clientele, or an inspirational meeting place for an instructor or speaker, or a clean, crisp canvas for a film producer who wants to creatively make it their own. We want your use of this space to be a reflection of you; transform it into something magical.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row]

item.title: Rental Policy
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
[vc_row][vc_column][vc_single_image image="98" img_size="full" alignment="center" el_class="inner-banner"][vc_row_inner el_class="inner-page-content"][vc_column_inner][vc_column_text el_class="inner-page-desc"]
  1. Your scheduled rental time begins promptly at the designated start time and ends promptly at the designated ending time. Be sure to schedule enough time to accommodate clients who may be running late, and any additional time that you may need to finish cleaning up. If your session runs over your rental period, you will automatically be charged another hour.
  2. Only one photographer is allowed per shoot. Styled shoots are welcome but pricing will be different to accommodate multiple photographers.  Mini-sessions or multi-client shoots are also welcome but priced differently.
  3. You are required to leave the studio space and client lounge exactly how you found it. Clean up after every shoot. This includes the white floors, walls, windows, all furniture pieces, bathroom, vanity area, kitchen area, etc. Failing to do may result in loss of your studio deposit or an invoice containing a separate cleaning fee.
  4. No smoking whatsoever is allowed in the building or within 20 feet of any entrance. Food and drink must stay in the client lounge area. Music/voices are to be kept at a reasonable level and not contain vulgar or offensive language or lyrics.
  5. No fires, candles or pets allowed at anytime unless with written permission from the studio manager. Glitter, cake smash sessions, sand, and anything that will stain white floors or walls are not allowed unless with special consent. No nails, pins, etc on the walls. If you need to adhere something, please use removable hooks or putty. If you damage the walls or space in any way, you are responsible for the repairs.
  6. Conduct: You are responsible for the conduct and welfare of all clients and persons accompanying you during your rental period. The studio manager reserves the right to cancel or terminate any scheduled session for any reason they deem necessary.
  7. 523studios require a COI certificate of insurance for all rentals. Your insurance company will need to list 523studios on your policy, and a copy of that certificate is required for rental.
  8. You are welcome to move any of the furniture or props in the space, but please do not drag the furniture across the floor. Please have someone help you move heavy items and make sure you put everything back into the place it was when you arrived.
  9. Cancellation: Cancellations of confirmed bookings will result in the following charges: If 72 hours or more prior to the rental date, you may reschedule the rental date within 4 weeks without penalty. If 48 – 72 hours prior to the rental date, then 50% of all payments will be refunded. If less than 48 hours prior to rental date, then no payments will be refunded.
  10. A $100 refundable security deposit is required to book. You will receive your check back or your credit card will be refunded back following your scheduled rental period provided there was no breach of contract and all of the studio policies were adhered.
[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row]

item.title: Sample Page
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
This is an example page. It's different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:

Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my website. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like piña coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)

...or something like this:

The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.

As a new WordPress user, you should go to your dashboard to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!

item.title: FAQ
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
[vc_row][vc_column][vc_single_image image="98" img_size="full" alignment="center" el_class="inner-banner"][vc_row_inner el_class="inner-page-content"][vc_column_inner][vc_custom_heading text="How much does it cost to rent?" font_container="tag:div|text_align:left" use_theme_fonts="yes" el_class="inner-page-title"][vc_column_text el_class="inner-page-desc"]For photographers, please visit our Studio Rates page to see a complete list of pricing.  For small events, workshops, and intimate gatherings – please inquire directly for special rates.[/vc_column_text][vc_custom_heading text="Is there a deposit required to book?" font_container="tag:p|text_align:left" use_theme_fonts="yes" el_class="inner-page-title"][vc_column_text el_class="inner-page-desc"]Payment for your studio rental is required in full to book your date. A $100 refundable security deposit is required on the day of your photo shoot. You will receive your check back or your credit card will be refunded back following your scheduled rental period provided there was no breach of contract and all of the studio policies were adhered.[/vc_column_text][vc_custom_heading text="What is your cancellation policy?" font_container="tag:p|text_align:left" use_theme_fonts="yes" el_class="inner-page-title"][vc_column_text el_class="inner-page-desc"]
Cancellations of confirmed bookings will result in the following charges:
If 72 hours or more prior to the rental date, then Client may reschedule the rental date within 1 month without penalty. If 48 – 72 hours prior to the rental date, then 50% of all payments will be refunded. If less than 48 hours prior to rental date, then no payments will be refunded.
[/vc_column_text][vc_custom_heading text="What is the recommended booking time for scheduled portrait and commercial shoots?" font_container="tag:p|text_align:left" use_theme_fonts="yes" el_class="inner-page-title"][vc_column_text el_class="inner-page-desc"]We recommend a 2 hour window for full portrait, bridal, or senior photo sessions.  For newborns, we recommend 3hours – half day. For commercial projects, we recommend booking by the full day.[/vc_column_text][vc_custom_heading text="What does my rental space and time consist of?" font_container="tag:p|text_align:left" use_theme_fonts="yes" el_class="inner-page-title"][vc_column_text el_class="inner-page-desc"]We have two options for booking our space: (1) 800SF All-White Studio: This rental space consists of the  all-white studio space, client lounge, and available studio props only. (2) 2500SF Exclusive Studio Access:  This rental space consists of private and exclusive access to the all-white studio space, client lounge, front production area, all studio props, office desks & client seating area. Plan your rental time such that you have allowed for set up, client meeting, session, and cleanup to happen within your rental time. Please also plan for your client arriving late or for your scheduled session running over. Arriving before your scheduled time to set up is not permitted, as another photographer may have the space during that time. Please note that extending your scheduled time will result in a 50% increase in hourly rate.  Plan time not only to break down any equipment you’ve used, but to also clean any messes and to sweep the floor.[/vc_column_text][vc_custom_heading text="Tell me about your 2500SF Exclusive Studio Access?" font_container="tag:p|text_align:left" use_theme_fonts="yes" el_class="inner-page-title"][vc_column_text el_class="inner-page-desc"]523studios shares a large (but separate) space with Alice Park Photography and NAPCP. This add on includes your use of the common space outside of the studio and beverage bar with the guarantee no one will be onsite except a Studio Manager. Certain areas of the office will be off limits. Rentals with over 10 people will be required to book this option. Any sessions including nudity (i.e. boudior), even for a portion of the session, are required to book this option. Rentals for mini sessions are highly encouraged to book this option to provide a space for clients in case of overlap.[/vc_column_text][vc_custom_heading text="What is prohibited in the space?" font_container="tag:p|text_align:left" use_theme_fonts="yes" el_class="inner-page-title"][vc_column_text el_class="inner-page-desc"]Please review all of our studio policies for a list of what is prohibited in 523studios.[/vc_column_text][vc_custom_heading text="Can I host parties or events in the space?" font_container="tag:p|text_align:left" use_theme_fonts="yes" el_class="inner-page-title"][vc_column_text el_class="inner-page-desc"]Yes, 523studios is available for small event rental.  Bridal lunches, birthday parties, corporate lunches, private receptions and even small weddings! Please inquire about your specific needs for event space rental[/vc_column_text][vc_custom_heading text="What time is the light the best?" font_container="tag:p|text_align:left" use_theme_fonts="yes" el_class="inner-page-title"][vc_column_text el_class="inner-page-desc"]We designed the space so that light is optimal no matter what time of the day. You will receive soft, even light from time the sun rises until about 2 hours before the sun begins to set (around 9am – 5pm). Because the studio is west facing, the light tends to be a little harsher in the late afternoon.[/vc_column_text][vc_custom_heading text="What types of props do you provide?" font_container="tag:p|text_align:left" use_theme_fonts="yes" el_class="inner-page-title"][vc_column_text el_class="inner-page-desc"]1. A linen tufted loveseat 2. A linen bench 3. An 8’x8’ movable wall with options of a charcoal gray or natural wood grain backdrop 4. A queen size bed with a linen headboard and white sheets 5. A white, modern Eames-style chair[/vc_column_text][vc_custom_heading text="How large is the rental space?" font_container="tag:p|text_align:left" use_theme_fonts="yes" el_class="inner-page-title"][vc_column_text el_class="inner-page-desc"]The natural light studio space is approximately 800 square feet. The client lounge area adjacent to the studio is approximately 150 square feet.[/vc_column_text][vc_custom_heading text="Tell me about the client lounge area?" font_container="tag:p|text_align:left" use_theme_fonts="yes" el_class="inner-page-title"][vc_column_text el_class="inner-page-desc"]Nestled right next to the studio space is a client lounge area that houses a custom-built vanity area, a small kitchenette, dining area for 4, children’s play area, and extra seating for additional guests. We designed it to make your clients feel right at home.[/vc_column_text][vc_custom_heading text="How do I book?" font_container="tag:p|text_align:left" use_theme_fonts="yes" el_class="inner-page-title"][vc_column_text el_class="inner-page-desc"]To reserve your desired date and time, please follow the below steps:
  1. Check out our Calendar here to see if the date and time you want is available. Remember that the Calendar is a planning tool only; your date is not guaranteed to be available.
  2. Each room rents by the full hour. Plan your rental time such that you have allowed for set up, your shoot/meeting, and cleanup to happen within your rental time. Arriving before your scheduled time to set up is not permitted, as another photographer may have the room during that time. Standard business hours are 9am – 6pm. Submit your reservation request.
  3. Once our team has reviewed your reservation request and confirmed your project adheres to our studio guidelines and policies, we will send you receive a contract to sign with a link to pay your deposit and studio rental fee. Both are required to secure your rental.
[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row]

item.title: viviana guerra event decor workshop
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: When Viviana Guerra asked to host her first ever workshop at 523studios, we had no hesitation in giving an enthusiastic “Yes!” to working closely with some amazing industry minds. This amazing workshop was a collaborative effort between several very talented people in event planning. We were honored to be the location for this very first workshop, and we cannot stop obsessing over the beautiful use of our space. It was such an honor to work with this these creatives! An experience filled with beautiful details, talented guest speakers, and group activities, all designed to help attendees elevate event design while building new skills, new relationships, and newfound confidence in themselves and their businesses. Such a cool opportunity, right?! Catch more details on Viviana Guerra Event Décor, on Instagram! Let’s start with this JAW DROPPING use of our space. We love how they used our white space for learning, and our reception area for meals. Pure magic. We were so in love with the natural light flooding our studio, perfectly complementing the pastel florals. So good, right?! We wish we could have flower arrangements like these in the studio every day. Perfection! Color combinations of light pinks, blush, coral, lilac, and hydrangea blue filled the tables, and exquisite sweets. This amazing workshop was a collaborative effort between several very talented people in event planning. We were honored to be the location for this very first workshop, and we cannot stop obsessing over the beautiful use of our space. It was such an honor to work with this these creatives! An experience filled with beautiful details, talented guest speakers, and group activities, all designed to help attendees elevate event design while building new skills, new relationships, and newfound confidence in themselves and their businesses. Such a cool opportunity, right?! Catch more details on Viviana Guerra Event Décor, on Instagram! Let’s start with this JAW DROPPING use of our space. We love how they used our white space for learning, and our reception area for meals. Pure magic. We were so in love with the natural light flooding our studio, perfectly complementing the pastel florals. So good, right?! We wish we could have flower arrangements like these in the studio every day. Perfection! Color combinations of light pinks, blush, coral, lilac, and hydrangea blue filled the tables, and exquisite sweets. What we loved most about this workshop is that the event design team used every bit of our studio space. We love meeting new creative friends! We’re looking forward to many more workshops!
